[The number of cases of legionnaires' disease in the South Bronx since 10 Jul 2015 has now risen to 71 with 4 deaths. 22 buildings in the South Bronx are said to have been visited; 17 buildings that have cooling towers have been tested for _Legionella_, with results back on 11; 5 buildings are positive for _Legionella_; and the results are pending for 6 other buildings. The positive sites are being remediated.

Genotyping is likely being done on the environmental and clinical isolates to see if there are any matching patterns. Clinical isolates with matching genotypes would suggest a common source for those cases and a cooling tower with an _Legionella_ isolate having a genotype that matches that of the clinical isolates would be the likely source. - Mod.ML

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3553750,1581.]
